The power density is another major factor to decide the performance of supercapattery. Merely it depends on voltage and equivalent series resistance (Rs\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$R_{\text{s}}$$\end{document}) of the cell. The minimization of the equivalent series resistance of the cell is another factor to maximize the power density, and it can be achieved by reducing the contact resistance between the active material and current collector. Hence, it must be achieved by the uniform deposition of active material on the current collector.
